node.text:
🍕Pizza or Ice Cream? 🍦
🏈NFL or Soccer? ⚽
👀Logan Paul or Jake Paul?
Think you know @kingryan? Think again... 🤯
We're catching up with Ryan Garcia to find out what really matters ahead of the biggest test of his career to date...
Ryan Garcia vs. Luke Campbell. 2nd January. 
The fight is on 🥊🔥
#Gymshark

node.text:
🔥 #Gymshark66 2021 is coming 🔥
Want to join in? 🙌
1. Decide on your 66-day pledge between now and 23:59 GMT on 31st December 📝
2. Show us your progress during the 66-day challenge between 1st January and 7th March 🗓
3. Be in with the chance to win super prizes, such as an EXCLUSIVE GYMSHARK EXPERIENCE 😱
4. Join in on weekly challenges for the chance to win limited edition Gymshark goodies 🦈
Got a question? Drop 'em below and we'll get back to ya 💪
For more information and T+Cs, head to the link in our bio 💻
#Gymshark

node.text:
Deload Sidekick @drmikethe2nd chats all things mental wellbeing and self-care during these tough times. 

World Mental Health Day with Dr Mike Banna intends to create positive, impactful change through conversation. The views and opinions expressed by the speaker within the IGTV are based on their own personal experiences. They do not reflect the views or opinions of Gymshark, nor do they provide medical advice. 
Have any further questions for Dr Mike? Let us know below ↓ 
#Gymshark

node.title: World Mental Health Day with Dr Mike Banna

node.text:
We asked @kennyethanjones (he/him) to share his fitness story with us, here's what he said 👇
"When I first started attending the gym it was from a place of curiosity. I saw the gym as the birthplace of masculinity and as a pre-testosterone trans man I never felt ‘enough’ on my own. I’d stare at the bodybuilders, imagining what it would be like to have chiselled chest. How powerful, and masculine, I would feel to be able to push the weight that they did. And so, my fitness journey began.

In the beginning it was uncomfortable and intimidating. I’d often receive glares because people were trying to figure out my gender. I had to wrap my binder extra tight in order to hide my chest and I could barely push any of the weights to begin with.

In time, fitness offered me more than I ever could have imagined. I had been born into a body I strongly disliked but the gym offered me the opportunity to sculpt my body, and for the first time I felt like I had some form of control. When I felt physically stronger, I felt mentally stronger too, so navigating body dysphoria and transphobia became a little bit easier. And finally, I gained a better connection with myself. Overall, fitness has helped boost my self-esteem and has been one of my self-care pillars".
#TogetherWeMove
#Gymshark

node.text:
“Be who you want to be. I am asked every day why I don’t get my skin removed, my answer, I don’t want to. Why is my hair blue? Because I want it to be. I think a lot of people feel like when you step outside of what is considered “normal” it’s because you want “attention” I disagree. I think doing what you want to do with your body, and life, is what freedom is all about. If you proclaim to live freedom, while simultaneously shaming anyone else who doesn’t fit into a “box” do you really love freedom? Do what you want for yourself, and be kind to others" 💙
We couldn't have put it better ourselves @obese_to_beast 👏
#Gymshark
